text: Just bought the hardcover + draft access üôå . I helped self-publish my partner's book this year, it can be very tedious. I ended up using Sigil for the ebook as it was the best way to avoid formatting issues on different e-readers. For print, Google Docs came with limited formatting options, so I had to transfer it to Word for mirrored margins, and my version kept crashing, so ended up writing my own very simple PDF formatting script with node.js that consumed the Google Docs version and formatted it for print with margins and numbering!
